-1.title: Cake Pipe (Tekkit Livestream #4)
-1.plot: The boys have challenged themselves to build in two hours what took over one hundred episodes to complete - they're building the Jaffa Factory from scratch. Will they make it in time?

1.title: Jaffa Cake Factory Planning
1.plot: Simon has set the task of building a factory to make delicious biscuits. He is joined by Duncan and Lewis to help make this dream a reality.

2.title: Raining Ladders
2.plot: Simon has set the task of building a factory to make delicious biscuits. He is joined by Duncan and Lewis to help make his dream a reality.

3.title: Fools Diamond
3.plot: Simon has set the task of building a factory to make delicious biscuits. He is joined by Duncan and Lewis to help make his dream a reality.

4.title: Pimp my Shed
4.plot: Simon has set the task of building a factory to make delicious biscuits. He is joined by Duncan and Lewis to help make his dream a reality.

5.title: Not Co?
5.plot: Simon, Lewis, and Duncan deal with and unexpected visitor as they begin to lay the foundations for their factory.

6.title: The Iron Door
6.plot: Whilst Sjin has a coffee break, the gang goes under cover and takes a look around Sips Co to see what's hiding in their work shed.

7.title: Magical Dust!
7.plot: Duncan and Lewis learn how to make some magical dust, whilst Simon attempts to protect the factory from unwanted guests.

8.title: Dirty Tricks
8.plot: Lewis and Duncan learn how to make some magical dust, whilst Simon attempts to protect the factory from unwanted guests.

9.title: Lighty Stone
9.plot: Duncan and Lewis learn how to make some magical dust, whilst Simon attempts to protect the factory from unwanted guests.

10.title: Inglourious Ghasterds
10.plot: Lewis, Simon, and Duncan travel into the nether to mine some precious ores. When they return with their goodies they get and unexpected surprise.

11.title: Simon's Close-up!
11.plot: The gang reduces their carbon footprint by planting some saplings, and finally get around to making a seedless farm.

12.title: The Jaffa Café
12.plot: The gang spends the day extending the height of their factory walls, and creating a piping system for their delicious Jaffas. They also spot something scary looming in the distance over at Sips Co.

13.title: Simon Goes Mad With Power
13.plot: Whilst Duncan and Lewis maneuver the quarry to the correct position, Simon watches over the busy workers, leading to something a little unexpected.

14.title: Work Experience
14.plot: Silk-shirt-guy arrives at Sips Co to apply for a job, whilst over at Honeydew Inc, they hire a new employee to help out with the workload.

15.title: Fishy Business
15.plot: Lewis starts filtering through dirt over at Sips co whilst learning the company motto, whilst Simon and Duncan continue to watch over their newly formed quarry. Neither company is aware of a new business that's just set up in town.

16.title: Rainbow Factory
16.plot: Simon and Duncan start to organize their chests and beautify the land around them, whilst over at Sips Co, Lewis is feeling the pressure as Sips goes frolicking through the wilderness.

17.title: New Beginnings
17.plot: Lewis creates something to simplify the dirt sorting in Sips Co, whilst over at Honeydew Corp/Inc/Enterprises, they notice things going missing from their work shed and suspect a thief in town.

18.title: Back To Work
18.plot: With the team back together, the boys get down to some actually productive work for once.

19.title: Statue of Sjin
19.plot: The boys get distracted by a strange distraction on the outskirts of the Jaffa Factory, but are inspired to continue onward with construction.

20.title: Out of the Comfort Zone
20.plot: The boys make and important transition from work-shed to factory, and realize quite how big and daunting their ambitions are.

21.title: Holiday
21.plot: Simon and Duncan are on vacation, so Lewis has been left with a list of jobs to complete. Fortunately, he finds someone to help out with all the jobs.

22.title: Swimming
22.plot: Having secured Sjin's help with the promise of half a share of Honeydew Inc, the pair get to work on locating and pumping oil.

23.title: Oil Island
23.plot: After wiping out the indigenous pig population of Oil Island, Lewis and Sjin get to work on the oil refinery.

24.title: Apple Sauce
24.plot: After wiping out the indigenous pig population of Oil Island, Lewis and Sjin get to work on the oil refinery.

25.title: A Job Well Done
25.plot: Construction at the oil refinery continues and Lewis and Sjin struggle with the complicated pipes and machinery.

26.title: Showing Off
26.plot: Simon returns home from his holiday and Lewis and Sjin get to impress him with all of their hard work on the oil refinery.

27.title: Tunneling
27.plot: Today the boys attempt to create a tunnel for pipe work back towards the Jaffa Factory.

28.title: The Piggs Boson
28.plot: The guys continue to pipe back their gasoline underground whilst singing karaoke songs, and attempting to beautify Pig Island.

29.title: Nerd Poles
29.plot: After a nice sleep, the boys discuss the next steps of the factory construction and have a little trouble with engines and pipes.

30.title: A Touch of Nature
30.plot: The boys try their best to repair the damage cause and travel back to the factory with everything they can carry, and are greeted by a visitor wanting to reclaim their goods.

31.title: Walled In
31.plot: The boys are all back to working on their projects and come across a few complications over the land.

32.title: Yellow Lanterns
32.plot: The guys get around to lighting up the Jaffa Factory with wonderful yellow lanterns.

33.title: Negapig!
33.plot: The guys take a sneaky look at the new flashing object over at Sips co, and finally get to see if the machines in the factory work.

34.title: Run.dmc
34.plot: The boys find something unexpected in their back garden and decide to investigate where it came from.

35.title: Don't Stop the Groove
35.plot: The boys get down to the nitty-gritty jobs finishing off the lighting and sort a few more quarries out for materials.

36.title: Spring Cleaning
36.plot: The boys do some excavation and start working on the Power Station underneath the factory.

37.title: What a Pavlova
37.plot: The boys get a few new quarries up and running and organize the pipes to keep the combustion engines cool.

38.title: Big Plans
38.plot: Lewis and Duncan resume work on the factory, while Simon's lack of sleep is causing strange side-effects.

39.title: Surveying The Island
39.plot: Lewis and Duncan continue their factory upgrades, while Sips and Sjin undertake a survey of Pig Island to assess its value.

40.title: More, More, More!
40.plot: Lewis and Duncan continue working on the factory whilst Simon returns with his precious dirt to start on his very important project.

41.title: Therapy
41.plot: Lewis comes up with an explosive idea to get the old Simon back - with a bit of therapeutic rest and relaxation.

42.title: Negotiations
42.plot: The boys wake up to find Simon missing, and a bit of a leak in the basement. Meanwhile, Sjin and Sips discuss their plans regarding Pig Island and a deal is struck.

43.title: Sorting
43.plot: Whilst Simon is away, Lewis and Duncan continue working on the Jaffa Factory and set about getting the kinks out of the sorting process.

44.title: No More Chests
44.plot: Lewis and Duncan finish up their new sorting contraption and find a couple pets huddling in the pipes to keep warm.

45.title: Template
45.plot: Sips and Sjin discuss their nefarious plans for Pig Island before meeting up with Simon for some fiddling about and general time-wasting while setting up some fancy equipment.

46.title: Power Walking!
46.plot: Sips and Sjin continue analyzing Pig Island with Simon, whilst Duncan and Lewis have an infestation of chickens.

47.title: Vanishing Coal!
47.plot: The survey equipment is finally fired up over on Pig Island, whilst Lewis and Duncan try and work out what's happening with their vanishing coal.

48.title: The Head of the Problem
48.plot: The cause of Simon's pig obsession is finally uncovered as he discovers that a strange construction has been talking to him whilst he sleeps.

49.title: Flooring, Armor and Emptious Holes
49.plot: Lewis and Duncan struggle to produce enough carbon plates to make full sets of Nano-Armor. Meanwhile, Simon, Sips and Sjin mess around on Pig Island.

50.title: Michael Porkinson
50.plot: Simon's rejuvenation of Pig Island begins, and Lewis and Duncan start to resemble the Power Rangers.

51.title: Tiki Bar Building
51.plot: Simon builds stuff on Pig Island. Lewis and Duncan prepare themselves for a visit.

52.title: Duncan vs Head
52.plot: The Sipsco Pool Bar sells its first pork sandwich. Lewis and Duncan finally uncover the reason behind Simon's madness.

53.title: Simon uses his head
53.plot: There is much to do at the factory now that Simon's mind is clear. The boys focus on the to-do list and get back to business.

54.title: Putting Sipsco to Work
54.plot: After taking the young and spunky Sips on board, Simon is willing to let bygones be bygones and recruits another stray to Honeydew Inc.

55.title: Lapotron 5000
55.plot: Sips and Sjin show off their building skills, while Simon finds inventive ways to clear the land of pesky trees, and Duncan comes up with a new motto for Honeydew Inc.

56.title: Jaffahampton
56.plot: Simon gets to work on building a small town outside the Jaffa factory. Meanwhile Sips, Sjin and Duncan work through the night to stop the brownouts and build the walls.

57.title: Teacup
57.plot: Lewis and Duncan ensure that the Jaffa Factory continues to take shape nicely, Sjin works on the roof, and Simon and Sips start to make Jaffahampton look brilliant.

58.title: Mustard and Mug
58.plot: The Jaffa Factory complex begins to take shape as Simon and Sips continue their work on Jaffahampton, Duncan completes the initial design for the Honeydew sign and Lewis finishes up some flying rings, making everyone's lives a lot easier.

59.title: Lights On
59.plot: Lewis and Sips continue working on Jaffahampton, Duncan and Sjin wire up the grid for the Honeydew sign, whilst Simon goes in search for cows and gets a surprise when he re-visits pig island.

60.title: Kegs and Cold War Talks
60.plot: Duncan and Simon get sidetracked making beer while Lewis and Sjin perform necessary maintenance on the factory and discuss plans for world domination.

61.title: Coffee Cravings
61.plot: Duncan, Sips and Simon are still hunting for cows to fix their coffee cravings, whilst Lewis and Sjin continue working on the essential items needed for the running of the factory.

62.title: Grinding Eyeballs
62.plot: Still feeling the heady effects of Duncan's coffee, Simon and Sips make a small garden to grow hops, while Lewis and Sjin tidy up and make a mass fabricator which will hopefully produce the finest cocoa beans on the planet.

63.title: Good Gyrations
63.plot: Simon, Duncan and Sips try out their beer to see how its progressing, whilst Lewis and Sjin map out the foundations for some interesting buildings.

64.title: Black Stuff
64.plot: The boys pick out some tasks to carry out around and on the factory, and taste their first batch of beer.

65.title: Rules of the Hot Tub
65.plot: Simon decides on the most important aspect of his penthouse and wastes no time getting to work. Meanwhile, Duncan and Lewis begin the construction of an automated wheat farm.

66.title: One Way Time Machine
66.plot: Simon's penthouse gets a bit of 70's loving from Sjin, while Duncan and Lewis wire up the automated wheat farm.

67.title: The Crusher
67.plot: Duncan and Lewis get their elaborate wheat contraption working, Sjin plays around with some seeds, and Simon prepares a mixing bowl for the Jaffa mix.

68.title: Stickopus
68.plot: The boys split into teams with Duncan and Simon planning the egg roller-coaster and Lewis, Sjin and Sips making ambitious plans for Jaffa Production.

69.title: Tetris Machine
69.plot: Lewis, Sjin and Sips play Tetris with an energy collector, whilst Simon and Duncan create a coke oven to create creosote oil.

70.title: Eggtastic
70.plot: Lewis, Sjin and Sips start to shape the new home for the chickens, whilst Duncan and Simon work out where to lay the new pipes.

71.title: Cow Slug
71.plot: Lewis, Sjin and Sips test out the suction in the chicken facility and make a start on the next building, whilst Duncan and Simon finish up their coke ovens.

72.title: The Nether Portal Mystery
72.plot: Construction at the Jaffa Factory continues, with Lewis, Sips and Sjin building more machinery outside and Simon and Duncan wrestling with Railcraft inside.

73.title: Spider Milk
73.plot: Various shenanigans occur in and around the Jaffa Factory as the boys continue to make progress. Apologies to any cows or slugs watching.

74.title: One Stack of Rails
74.plot: Lewis, Sjin and Sips manage to get their first bucket of milk with their contraption whilst Simon and Duncan create their first set of rails.

75.title: Freezing up
75.plot: Christmas has hit Honeydew Inc and the boys start work decorating the Jaffa Factory and building the freezer level.

76.title: Bin Chute
76.plot: After the boys have a bit of a sing-song on the roof with some familiar explosive friends, they set to work about creating a recycling bin chute, whilst Simon and Sips have a snowball fight.

77.title: Santa Claws
77.plot: Christmas is coming to. Honeydew Inc. The Santa statue begins to take shape, the boys decorate a tree and have snow ball fights.

78.title: Diggy Ho Ho Ho
78.plot: The Santa statue is completed with one extra special addition.

79.title: Ice Wolf
79.plot: It's Christmas Day. The boys put the finishing touches on some creations in the Jaffa Factory, and prepare for the next phase of construction.

80.title: Diamond Stacks
80.plot: The boys return to the facility after Christmas and set about getting back to work. They discover a nice surprise waiting on top of the tree.

81.title: But But But
81.plot: Construction on the factory continues and a chicken harvesting system is developed.

82.title: Chicken Trouble
82.plot: Simon and Duncan try to work out why the chickens are all huddled in a corner and attempt to fix things, whilst Lewis, Sjin and Sips make some progress on the Jaffa Factory.

83.title: Cool and Fresh
83.plot: With the cookies sorted, Lewis, Sips and Sjin embark on the enormous task of cakes, meanwhile Simon has aspirations of becoming Isambard Kingdom Brunel and gets to work on the Honeydew Inc Great Egg Railway.

84.title: Decontamination Shower
84.plot: After tasting the first Jaffa, Lewis, Sips and Sjin decide to build a decontamination shower to ensure the purest Jaffas are created, whilst Simon and Duncan make progress on the Great Egg Railway.

85.title: The Great Egg Railway
85.plot: Simon and Duncan continue to make progress testing their track layout, whilst Lewis, Sjin and Sips finish up the piping to mass produce delicious Jaffas.

86.title: Mana From The Heavens
86.plot: Duncan and Simon try to calculate how to get their cart in the correct place when some mysterious Jaffas fall from the heavens.

87.title: Chest Test
87.plot: Simon and Duncan initiate the testing of the tracks whilst Lewis, Sips and Sjin prepare the factory for the eggs arrival.

88.title: Keep Calm & Eat Jaffas
88.plot: Simon and Duncan set up the last of the rails whilst Sjin and Lewis prepare the area for milking the cows.

89.title: Big Messy Machines
89.plot: The boys take a look at their to do list and discover that they have already managed to make a lot of progress. The factory is nearly ready to enter production.

90.title: Magicoal
90.plot: Duncan continues to work out where where the Great Egg Railway is going to run, whilst Lewis fixes up the missing lights, and Sips creates a road for the delivery trucks to arrive to ship out delicious Jaffas.

91.title: The Man
91.plot: Sips organizes the delivery area for the lorries to collect the Jaffas, whilst Lewis works on the broken bin chute. Simon decides to convert Santa into something new, whilst Duncan makes a start on the dual cart system for the eggs.

92.title: Finishing Touches
92.plot: Today's the day the boys put the final touches in place and switch on the factory to make delicious Jaffas. Will their hard work pay off?

93.title: Everything is Broken
93.plot: The Jaffa Factory has been updated to a new version, and the boys assess how much damage the factory has sustained in the changeover and what mods are missing from the pack.

94.title: Outpost Gamma
94.plot: The boys take a look at some of the newly generated parts of the world and attempt to work out what everything is.

95.title: Bee Hunting
95.plot: The boys continue to take a look around and try to gather up as many bees as they can.

96.title: Riches from the Deep
96.plot: The Green Lantern, Maroon Man, and Melon-suit guy resume work on Site Bee and start mapping out their surroundings.

97.title: Bee Pasty
97.plot: The boys continue to plan the layout of their bee facility and wrestle with building the things they need.

98.title: Bunny Slippers
98.plot: The boys continue to plan the layout of their bee facility and wrestle with building the things they need.

99.title: Runner Bees
99.plot: The boys gather up all the bees they have found and start to work out what types of bees they would like to produce.

100.title: Bee Movie
100.plot: The boys are making progress with their bee production facility whilst trying to find a new source of energy to generate the machines needed.

101.title: Treealyzer
101.plot: Things are proceeding nicely at Site B, the new production facility as we source a new means of power and fiddle about with trees.

102.title: Corgis & Shetland Ponies
102.plot: The boys continue with their cross pollination producing some beautiful cherry trees, whilst Sjin and Duncan continue building a facility to generate the power they need.

103.title: Cherry Trees
103.plot: The boys continue with their cross pollination producing some beautiful cherry trees, whilst Sjin and Duncan continue building a facility to generate the power they need.

104.title: Sigourney Weaver
104.plot: The cast continue doing stuff with bees and discuss something to do with Sigourney Weaver.

105.title: Lemon Trees
105.plot: Simon, Lewis and Sips take a look at their beautiful cherry trees and and hope for some more cross breeding whilst Sjin and Duncan cross their fingers and hope that the tank will fix its-self.

106.title: Green Tea
106.plot: Duncan finally works out that he needs some glass for the tank to work, and Sjin has some dark thoughts with a chainsaw. Simon, Lewis and Sips discuss the physics of Minecraft whilst pollinating trees and cutting the grass.

107.title: The Wizards Apprentice
107.plot: The boys bring some more workers on board to help then with Site Bee and try to work out how to balance the overflowing sea of bees whilst Duncan teaches Simon the ways of the Wizard.

108.title: Magical Powers
108.plot: The boys bring some more workers on board to help then with Site Bee and try to work out how to balance the overflowing sea of bees whilst Duncan teaches Simon the ways of the Wizard.

109.title: Bee Hitler
109.plot: Lewis and Sjin try to fix the swarm of bees slowly taking over Site Bee, whilst Simon does some research with Duncan and gets to set up his cauldron.

110.title: The Worst Witch
110.plot: The bee swarm is finally under control which enables Sjin and Lewis to focus on new projects, whilst Simon and Duncan make a start with their research.

111.title: Magical Farts
111.plot: The bee swarm is finally under control which enables Sjin and Lewis to focus on new projects, whilst Simon and Duncan make a start with their research.

112.title: Thieving Golem
112.plot: Lewis and Duncan start planning out how to progress over at site bee. They set to work on powering things up, whilst a crafty little golem stores away their materials.

113.title: Pulverizer
113.plot: Rewiring at Site B continues as Lewis fiddles around grafting the trees and Duncan gathers resources to make electrum ingots and redstone electricity conduits.

114.title: Bull Pine
114.plot: Rewiring at Site B continues as Lewis fiddles around grafting the trees and Duncan gathers resources to make electrum ingots and redstone electricity conduits.

115.title: Jaffa Power
115.plot: Lewis and Duncan set up the tesseracts and engines and get Jaffa power flowing through all of Site Bee.

116.title: Angry Man
116.plot: Lewis and Duncan set up the tesseracts and engines and get Jaffa power flowing through all of Site Bee.

117.title: Tingly Lasers
117.plot: The guys manage to make a laser to help them craft some redstone items to help them craft the items they need to power Site Bee efficiently.

imdb.plot outline: The Yogscast boys Xephos, Honeydew and Lividcoffee is on a quest to create a Jaffa cake factory known as Honeydew Inc in the plains. But little do they know a rivalry Dirt Factory is opening across the plains known as Sipsco with Sips_ as CEO and President of Sipsco and his companion Sjin. With Lewis Brindley as Xephos, the brain of the company. Simon Lane as Honeydew, the mindless dwarf with his love for digging holes and Jaffa Cakes. Duncan Jones as Lividcoffee, the mad scientist and probably the only one who knows what to do. Chris Lovasz as Sips_ the CEO and President of Sipsco and his fellow friend Paul Sykes as Sjin. Friends becomes enemies and enemies becomes friends, join this amazing adventure by the Yogscast.
